      type: "poem",
      title: "The Forest's Digital Symphony",
      description: "A young fox and her woodland friends discover an ancient grove where nature and technology harmonize, teaching them that modern passions can coexist beautifully with the natural world.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-a8a2146a4f36.svg",
      character: {"name": "Luna", "identity": "The curious fox who bridges ancient forests and modern dreams", "special": "She codes by moonlight, turning algorithms into nature’s melodies", "personality_tags": ["Creative", "Dreamy"]},
      addedAt: "2026-02-16",
      text: "In the heart of the Pacific Northwest,\nWhere cedars touch the clouded sky,\nLive creatures with a modern quest—\nTo blend old wisdom with WiFi.\n\nLuna the fox codes by moonlight,\nWhile Sage the owl debugs her dreams,\nAnd River the raccoon streams midnight\nNature documentaries by streams.\n\nTogether they seek the Digital Grove,\nWhere legend says the ancients planned\nA place where circuits learn to love\nThe rhythm of the living land.\n\nThrough fern-filled paths and mossy stones,\nThey follow signals in the breeze,\nUntil they find where nature owns\nThe harmony of code and trees.\n\nHere algorithms dance with rain,\nAnd servers hum like cricket songs,\nProof that progress need not stain\nThe world where every heart belongs.\n\nSo rest now, knowing dreams can weave\nTechnology with nature's art,\nAnd every passion we believe\nCan honor both the mind and heart.",
      target_age: 12,
      duration: 2,
