      type: "poem",
      title: "Nayeli's Arctic School Discovery",
      description: "A brave Inuit girl discovers a magical ice school where polar animals gather to learn together in the snowy wilderness.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-b8847383ab32.svg",
      character: {"name": "Nayeli", "identity": "A fearless Arctic explorer who uncovers hidden wonders in the snow", "special": "She finds secret places where animals learn and share magic under the stars", "personality_tags": ["Brave", "Curious"]},
      addedAt: "2026-02-16",
      text: "Long ago in the Arctic white,\nLived Nayeli, brave and bright.\nWith her sealskin boots so warm,\nShe walked through each snowy storm.\n\nOne day while hunting for her meal,\nShe found tracks that looked so real.\nPolar bear paws in the snow,\nWhere could they possibly go?\n\nFollowing prints both big and small,\nShe climbed up an icy wall.\nThere behind the frozen peak,\nShe found what she came to seek.\n\nA school made of crystal ice,\nWhere animals learned so nice!\nBear cubs counting fish to eat,\nSeals learning to swim so neat.\n\nArctic foxes shared their food,\nWhile walruses played and wooed.\nNayeli watched with wonder deep,\nAs creatures learned before they sleep.\n\nNow when stars begin to glow,\nShe dreams of that school of snow.\nWhere all creatures, big and small,\nLearn together, one and all.",
