      title: "Nayak and the Forgotten Ice Garden",
      description: "A young Inuit boy discovers a magical ice garden beneath his family's igloo, learning that nature's most precious treasures are often hidden in plain sight.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-2fedd4d6a646.svg",
      character: {"name": "Nayak", "identity": "A gentle explorer who finds magic in the world beneath his feet", "special": "He discovers hidden wonders where others see only snow and ice", "personality_tags": ["Curious", "Gentle"]},
      addedAt: "2026-02-16",
      text: "Deep in the Arctic, where snowflakes dance,\nLived young Nayak in his family's stance,\nAn igloo warm with seal oil light,\nThat glowed like stars throughout the night.\n\nOne morning while his parents slept,\nNayak found a crack that wept,\nWith crystal drops of purest blue,\nThat sparkled with a magic hue.\n\nHe followed down the icy trail,\nThrough passages both narrow and frail,\nUntil he found a garden bright,\nWith frozen flowers, pure delight.\n\nIce tulips bloomed in silver rows,\nAnd crystal trees where arctic wind blows,\nThis secret world beneath their home,\nWhere winter's children freely roam.\n\nHe climbed back up with wonder true,\nTo share this gift of arctic blue,\nFor nature keeps her treasures near,\nIn places that we hold most dear.\n\nNow Nayak dreams of gardens white,\nBeneath his family's loving light,\nWhere magic sleeps in ice and snow,\nAnd peaceful winter breezes blow.",
      target_age: 7,
      duration: 2,
