      text: "[RHYTHMIC] Comet twirls in the night so high,\nDancing where the fireflies fly.\nShe hums a tune, so soft, so bright,\nA silver trail—oh, what a sight!\n[PAUSE]\n\n[GENTLE] Below, the dinosaurs play,\nIn valleys green and rivers gray.\nThey wave their tails and laugh with glee,\n\"Come join us, Comet! Come, we plea!\"\n[PAUSE]\n\n[JOYFUL] She swoops down low with golden light,\nPainting stars on leaves so tight.\nThey chase her glow, they spin, they run,\nA game of joy—oh, what fun!\n[PAUSE]\n\n[CALM] The moon smiles wide, the wind sings sweet,\nAs Comet rests on clouds so neat.\n\"You’re my friend now,\" she whispers low,\n\"Together we’ll forever glow.\"\n[PAUSE]\n\n[WHISPERING] The world below grows still and deep,\nAs little eyes begin to sleep.\nComet hums one last soft tune,\nBeneath the watchful, loving moon.\n[PAUSE]\n\n[SLEEPY] Now close your eyes, my little dear,\nDream of skies so bright and clear.\nComet’s glow will guard your rest,\nA friend above—you’re loved the best.",
