      type: "story",
      title: "Sky’s First Warm Feather",
      description: "A little eagle chick discovers the warmth of family love as her feathers grow soft and strong under the Arctic sky.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-b5438a861ba4.svg",
      character: {"name": "Sky", "identity": "A gentle little explorer discovering love and strength in her world", "special": "Her feathers grow warm and strong, showing her family’s love helps her fly", "personality_tags": ["Curious", "Gentle"]},
      addedAt: "2026-02-21",
      text: "[GENTLE] High on a snowy cliff, in a cozy nest made of twigs and moss, lived a little eagle chick named Sky.\n\nShe had fluffy gray feathers, bright round eyes, and a heart full of wonder. Every morning, she would peek over the edge of her nest and watch the world below.\n\n[CALM] Mama Eagle would wrap her big wings around Sky and sing a soft song. 'You are safe, my little one,' she would whisper. 'You are loved.'\n\n[CURIOUS] One chilly morning, Sky noticed something new. Her feathers felt warmer than ever before! She wiggled her tiny wings and giggled. 'Mama, look! My feathers are changing!'\n\n[JOYFUL] Mama Eagle smiled and nuzzled her chick. 'Yes, my dear. Your feathers are growing strong and soft, just like my own. Soon, you will fly with me under the golden sun.'\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] Papa Eagle soared high above them, calling out in a proud voice. 'Sky, you are growing braver every day! Soon, you will dance with the wind.'\n\n[SLEEPY] As the sun dipped below the horizon, Sky snuggled close to her mama. The Arctic sky glowed pink and purple, and the world grew quiet. 'I love you, Mama,' Sky murmured, her eyes growing heavy.\n\nMama Eagle tucked her wings around her little chick. 'And I love you, my Sky. Always.' The wind hummed a lullaby, and Sky drifted off to sleep, warm and safe in her family’s love.",
