      addedAt: "2026-02-23",
      text: "[GENTLE] Deep, deep in the ocean, where the water is as blue as the sky at twilight, there lived a little jellyfish named Lumi. \n\nLumi wasn’t like the other jellyfish. She had a special glow, soft and warm, like a tiny lantern in the dark. Every night, she would float near the surface, watching the stars twinkle above the waves. [PAUSE] But tonight, something felt different. \n\n[CURIOUS] Lumi wiggled her tentacles and tilted her head. \"What’s that?\" she wondered. Below her, the water was shimmering with tiny lights—like hundreds of fireflies dancing in the sea. [EXCITED] Lumi’s glow pulsed brighter with excitement. \"I have to see!\" she said. \n\n[CHAR_START]\"Here I go!\"[CHAR_END] Lumi fluttered downward, her tentacles trailing behind her like ribbons. The deeper she went, the warmer the water felt, wrapping around her like a cozy blanket. [PAUSE] And then—oh!—she saw it. \n\n[JOYFUL] A whole field of glowing sea flowers! Their petals sparkled in blues and greens and pinks, swaying gently with the tide. Lumi giggled and twirled in circles, her glow matching the flowers’ shimmer. [CHAR_START]\"It’s so beautiful!\"[CHAR_END] she said, her voice bubbly with joy. \n\n[CURIOUS] But wait—what was that sound? A soft *plink-plink* like raindrops on a pond. Lumi turned her head. \"Can you hear that?\" she asked the sea flowers. They swayed silently, their petals rustling. [PAUSE] Lumi floated closer. \n\n[EXCITED] There, in the center of the glowing flowers, was a tiny shell. And from inside the shell came the *plink-plink* sound—like music! Lumi’s eyes widened. [CHAR_START]\"Hello?\"[CHAR_END] she called softly. The shell didn’t answer, but the music grew louder, sweeter. It filled the water around her, warm and gentle, like a lullaby. \n\n[GENTLE] Lumi curled her tentacles around herself, listening. The music made her feel safe, like she was wrapped in a hug. The glowing flowers swayed closer, their lights pulsing in time with the melody. [PAUSE] Lumi’s eyelids grew heavy. \"This is the best place ever,\" she whispered. \n\n[PHASE_2]\n\n[CALM] The music from the shell wrapped around Lumi like a soft blanket. She floated slowly, her tentacles drifting in the water. [BREATH_CUE] She took a big breath in—*whoosh*—filling her tiny body with warm, salty air. And then she let it out—*ahhh*—slow and steady, like the tide going out. \n\n[SLEEPY] The glowing flowers around her seemed to hum along with the shell’s music. Lumi stretched her tentacles wide, then let them go floppy, swaying gently. [PAUSE] She yawned a great big yawn, her glow dimming just a little. \"I’m so sleepy,\" she murmured. \n\n[CHAR_START]\"Maybe I should rest here,\"[CHAR_END] Lumi whispered to the sea flowers. They nodded their glowing petals, as if to say, \"Yes, little one. Stay awhile.\" \n\n[GENTLE] Lumi curled herself into a tiny ball, her tentacles tucking in close. The water around her felt warmer now, like a bath just the right temperature. [BREATH_CUE] She breathed in deep—*whoosh*—and out—*ahhh*—letting her body sink a little lower. \n\n[SLEEPY] The music from the shell grew softer, slower. Lumi’s glow pulsed in time with it, dimming and brightening, dimming and brightening. [PAUSE] Her eyelids fluttered. She was so warm, so heavy, so cozy. \n\n[CALM] The sea flowers swayed around her, their petals brushing against her tentacles like a lullaby. Lumi sighed, her body relaxing deeper into the water. [BREATH_CUE] One more big breath in—*whoosh*—and out—*ahhh*. Her glow flickered, then steadied, soft and gentle. \n\n[PHASE_3]\n\n[SLEEPY] Lumi was floating now, so softly, so slowly. The water held her like a cradle, rocking her side to side. [LONG_PAUSE] The glowing flowers around her pulsed one by one... dim... bright... dim... bright... each one soft and quiet. \n\n[WHISPERING] Warm... so warm... the water wrapped around her like a blanket. [LONG_PAUSE] Heavy... so heavy... her little body sinking just a little deeper. \n\n[SLEEPY] The shell’s music was a whisper now, a hum in the water. [LONG_PAUSE] Lumi’s glow dimmed... dimmed... until it was just a tiny spark, flickering like a star. \n\n[WHISPERING] Soft... so soft... the sea flowers swaying, swaying. [LONG_PAUSE] Safe... so safe... the water holding her close. \n\n[SLEEPY] Her eyelids grew heavier... heavier... until they closed gently, like petals at night. [LONG_PAUSE] The music faded... faded... until there was only silence. \n\n[WHISPERING] Warm... and safe... and sleepy... [LONG_PAUSE] Lumi’s glow flickered once more... then went out. [LONG_PAUSE] \n\n[WHISPERING] The ocean held her... so gently... so softly... [LONG_PAUSE] \n\n[WHISPERING] Sleep now... little one... [LONG_PAUSE] \n\n[WHISPERING] Sleep... [LONG_PAUSE]",
      lullaby_lyrics: "[verse]\nLumi glows in the ocean deep,\nDancing where the sea flowers sleep.\nSoft and warm, her light so bright,\nGuiding you through the starry night.\n\n[chorus]\nGlow, glow, little light so sweet,\nRock, rock, in the ocean's beat.\nDream, dream, under the tide,\nSleep now, safe inside.\n\n[verse]\nThe shell sings a lullaby,\nSoft and low, it hums the sky.\nClose your eyes and drift away,\nTo the music of the bay.\n\n[chorus]\nGlow, glow, little light so sweet,\nRock, rock, in the ocean's beat.\nDream, dream, under the tide,\nSleep now, safe inside.\n\n[verse]\nThe water holds you, warm and near,\nLike a blanket, soft and clear.\nLet the tide sing you to rest,\nIn the ocean's cozy nest.\n\n[chorus]\nGlow, glow, little light so sweet,\nRock, rock, in the ocean's beat.\nDream, dream, under the tide,\nSleep now, safe inside.",
