      addedAt: "2026-02-27",
      text: "[RHYTHMIC]High on a shelf, so dusty and old,\nLumi the lantern dreamed stories untold.\nHer glass was warm, her glow soft and bright,\nLike moonlight dancing on waves in the night.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[GENTLE]One morning she heard a small sigh,\nA girl named Mira, with eyes wide and shy.\n\"First day of school,\" she whispered low,\n\"But the path is dark—I don’t want to go.\"\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[JOYFUL]Lumi winked then, her flame burning true,\n\"I’ll light your way! Let’s see what we’ll do!\"\nDown from the shelf with a *clink* and a cheer,\nThey set off together—no need for fear.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[CALM]Past coconut trees and shells in the sand,\nPast crabs who waved with a claw so grand.\nThe waves hummed soft, the breeze sang sweet,\nAs Lumi’s glow made the path complete.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[WHISPERING]At school’s bright door, Mira turned with a grin,\n\"You’ll come tomorrow?\" Lumi nodded within.\n\"For every new friend who feels lost or small,\nI’ll shine my light—it’s the best gift of all.\"\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[SLEEPY]Now Lumi rests, her flame burning low,\nDreaming of tides and the friends she’ll know.\nFor lanterns don’t sleep when the world feels new—\nThey wake with the dawn to guide *you* too.",
