      addedAt: "2026-03-01",
      text: "[SINGING] Finn swims soft in the silver light,\n[SINGING] Moonbeams dance on the water bright.\n[SINGING] Through the reeds where the fireflies play,\n[SINGING] He hums a tune to end the day.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[HUMMING] Hmm, hmm, hmm, the lagoon sings back,\n[HUMMING] Ripples shimmer, no need to slack.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[JOYFUL] Oh, little fish, oh, sleepy crab,\n[JOYFUL] The tide will tuck you in your lab.\n[JOYFUL] The stars will watch from up so high,\n[JOYFUL] And keep you safe ‘til morning’s nigh.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[GENTLE] Finn glides past the whispering stones,\n[GENTLE] Where ancient turtles rest their bones.\n[GENTLE] The wind hums low, the waves agree,\n[GENTLE] The world is soft as soft can be.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[SLEEPY] Now home he swims, so warm, so near,\n[SLEEPY] His family waits, their love so clear.\n[SLEEPY] The lagoon rocks them, side by side,\n[SLEEPY] Drifting off on the evening tide.",
