      addedAt: "2026-03-02",
      text: "[SINGING] Way up high in a silver cloud,\nDrizzle hums a sleepy sound.\nMonsoon friends all snuggle tight,\nBut one small drop wants soft moonlight.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[HUMMING] Hmm hmm hmm, hmm hmm hmm...\n\n[SINGING] Down he falls on neon beams,\nPast the towers, past the dreams.\nCars like stars all twinkle low,\nWhere does gentle glimmer go?\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[JOYFUL] Oh, the park has firefly trees,\nDancing lights on rustling leaves!\nDrizzle giggles, spins around,\nGlow so warm right off the ground.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[GENTLE] He collects the light so sweet,\nTucked inside his tiny feet.\nUp he floats on silver breeze,\nBack to friends who long for ease.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[SLEEPY] Now the cloud is soft and bright,\nEvery drop curls in the light.\nDrizzle hums a lullaby,\nDreaming ‘neath the neon sky.",
