      type: "song",
      title: "Pebble’s Floating School of Starlight",
      description: "Beneath a sky of swirling neon auroras, the ocean hums with floating classrooms made of coral and light. When the tide carries away Pebble’s favorite learning shell, she must journey across glowing waves to find it—before the school drifts too far into the horizon.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-c8ac4b389df1.svg",
      addedAt: "2026-03-05",
      text: "[SINGING] The waves go shhh, the waves go shine,\nPebble listens, soft and fine.\n[GENTLE] Shells all sing in colors bright,\nLessons float in starry light.\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[HUMMING] Hmm-hmm-hmm, hmm-hmm-hmm...\n\n[SINGING] One small shell, her favorite one,\nSlipped away—oh, what’s to be done?\n[JOYFUL] Drift and glide on moonlit beams,\nFind the shell with gentle dreams!\n\n[PAUSE]\n\n[HUMMING] Hmm-hmm-hmm, hmm-hmm-hmm...\n\n[SLEEPY] Now the shell is back once more,\nSafe and snug on ocean’s floor.\n[GENTLE] Pebble smiles, the stars align,\nLearning shines in starlight time.",
