      type: "story",
      title: "Tilly and the Glowing Coral Cradle",
      description: "Beneath the shimmering twilight waves, tiny glowing corals begin to hum with soft light. Tilly the little sea turtle feels a gentle pull to build something special with her father—something that will make their ocean home even brighter.",
      cover: "/covers/gen-b12dc68672e3.svg",
      addedAt: "2026-03-07",
      text: "[GENTLE] Deep, deep in the ocean, where the water turns from blue to purple, lived a little sea turtle named Tilly.\n\n[CALM] Every evening, she loved to float beside her father, watching the glowing corals light up like tiny stars.\n\n[CURIOUS] 'Papa,' Tilly whispered, 'why do the corals glow so softly?'\n\n[WHISPERING] 'They’re singing to the ocean, my dear,' Papa said. 'And tonight, we can help them sing even brighter.'\n\n[ADVENTUROUS] Together, they gathered tiny, glowing pieces of coral and sea glass, weaving them into a cradle of light.\n\n[JOYFUL] As they worked, fish and jellyfish gathered around, their own lights flickering in time with the corals. [laugh] 'It’s a lullaby of light!' Tilly giggled.\n\n[SLEEPY] When the cradle was finished, Tilly curled up inside, her shell warm and safe. The ocean hummed its softest song, and the lights glowed just for her, like a family’s love wrapping her in golden dreams.",
